textRun.content: Document Import — Nested Structures & References Test

This document is intended to test the importer’s ability to handle nested structures, including multi-level lists, deeply nested headings, and references to other documents. It also includes cases that exceed normal nesting depth to ensure the importer gracefully handles limits.
This section demonstrates heading depth beyond normal content structures.
This section includes references to other test documents used in the suite. These references should be detected and represented as relationships or cross-links in Contentful.

Nested content should be preserved up to the supported depth. Any content exceeding nesting or reference depth limits should be handled gracefully. Circular references should be detected and safely ignored or reported without breaking import.
